The police in Westenburg outside Polokwane have arrested
an off-duty Traffic Officer Â who shot and
injured a teenage girl. Police spokesperson Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said the
incident occurred on Wednesday at around 12:30 in the afternoon at Greenside
between Ext 44 and 40. Ngoepe said It is alleged that three girls aged 13, 15
and 17, were walking along a street when the 42-year-old cop suspect insulted
them. An exchange of words ensued between the man and the
youngsters until he chased after them in his car. He said the cop apparently fired several shots in the
direction of the children injuring a 17-year-old girl in the process. The Police and the Medical Emergency Services were
summoned and immediately responded. The cop was arrested his firearm was confiscated. The victim was rushed to the local hospital where she was
treated and is recovering at home. Ngoepe said further police investigations are still being
conducted to establish the circumstances around the shooting. "Legal gun owners are reminded to always comply with
the provisions of the Firearm Controls Act. Any contravention of this Act may
result in the owner being declared unfit to possess a firearm in addition to
the criminal charges that will be pressed against them," said Ngoepe. The suspect will appear in the Polokwane Magistrate's
Court soon on a charge of attempted murder.